or distribution. Overall, our findings\nindicate that when the available training set is relatively small (75 - to 500\ninput - output examples) and fixed beforehand, DNNs can well emulate RTMs but\nare not suited to emulation-based inversion. In contrast, GPs perform fairly\nwell across all considered tasks: direct emulation, GSA, UP, and inversion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 19 Sep 2018 17:27:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 1 Jul 2019 08:59:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-02"}
